# Build the voice escalation adapter

## Step

Day-two, deliberately **not a cutover gate**: the host-resident agent invokes today's `call-joel` CLI at cutover with today's proof level. Chartered behind cutover so it is not lost (Joel: "we want voice so don't lose it").

Spec is the proposed interface in [`asset-voice-escalation-seam.svx`](./asset-voice-escalation-seam.svx): one host-side adapter on flagg wrapping the existing `call-joel.sh` mechanics into an idempotent, correlated action —

- `CallJoel({ escalationId, reason, origin })` → `answered | unanswered | failed` with typed failure stage.
- Truthful `answered` requires both facts: SIP leg answered **and** the voice worker joined the same room (worker appends the join with the same `escalationId`).
- Participant attributes carry `escalationId`, `call_reason`, origin correlation; lifecycle facts append to the stream.
- New semantic contract (e.g. `voice/escalation.requested`) — never overload `notification/call.requested` (one-way TeXML + SMS). `call-joel` CLI survives as a wrapper over the same adapter.
- The adapter owns mechanics only; urgency, retry, timing, wording, and fallback stay agent judgments. Reject duplicate `escalationId`; redact numbers/secrets from receipts.

Resolved when a gateway-initiated escalation produces the full correlated lifecycle in the stream (requested → answered-with-worker-join → completed) on a real call, and `call-joel` rides the adapter.
